rstmals historisch-kritisch ediert, wobei die Identifikation benutzter Quellen einen Schwerpunkt bildet.  aThis volume focuses on two extensive publications and an undated manuscript: the Holy Family written by Marx and Engels, the Condition of the Working Class in England by Engels, and the undated, fragmentary “Draft on Friedrich List” by Marx. In addition, there are 21 articles by Engels, including the “Speeches in Elberfeld”, and three articles and one declaration by Marx.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEconomics. 0aSocialism. 4aEngels, Friedrich. 4aMarx, Karl. 4aPolitische Ideengeschichte. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aFriedrich Engels.  aKarl Marx.  ahistory of political ideas.1 aRoth, Regina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeckwerth, Christine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMEGA Prepaid 1975-2032z9783110691986oZDB-23-GKO0 cprintz978311068326440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311068341740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110683417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110683417/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GKOc1975d2032